{"tag_name":"v0.1","target_commitish":"main","name":"Release v0.1","body":"### Release v0.1 (Pre-release)\nThis is the first official release of the **Chess Engine Core**. It introduces the foundational elements of a Rust-based chess engine designed to support UCI (Universal Chess Interface) and future extensions.\n\n#### **Highlights**\n- **Initial Core Implementation:**\n  - Introduced a Rust-based chess engine with the **alpha-beta search algorithm**.\n  - Added a flexible **personality system** to support custom play styles.\n  - Integrated with the **UCI protocol**, enabling compatibility with major chess GUIs.\n  ([Initial Commit](https://github.com/SrihariLegend/chess-engine-core/commit/932f530d20992b382eeb8293deb8360a4a267542))\n\n- **Enhancements:**\n  - Added a comprehensive `.gitignore` tailored for Rust projects.\n  ([Commit](https://github.com/SrihariLegend/chess-engine-core/commit/03153916b806faed10d5af836ba8484773703bc4))\n  - Updated **board and search modules** for better modularity and performance.\n  ([Commit](https://github.com/SrihariLegend/chess-engine-core/commit/b925e6ac3e8681ace6312979f92639ae3d72b88f))\n\n- **Cleanups:**\n  - Removed legacy files (e.g., `engine-settings.json`) deemed unnecessary.\n  ([Commit](https://github.com/SrihariLegend/chess-engine-core/commit/ce07912cd277917bfcc4b2ba573e62886a49184a))\n  - Deleted outdated compiled releases.\n  ([Commit](https://github.com/SrihariLegend/chess-engine-core/commit/762f48be0141eb1a61b5f48cf4696ca04dc96028))\n\n#### **Next Steps**\n- Continue development with a focus on optimization and new features.\n- Gather community feedback to guide future iterations.\n\n**Note:** This is a **pre-release**, meaning it's an early version and may require further stability and optimization before production use.","draft":false,"prerelease":true}